<br>
If you really wanted to pull a single you could even enstill the two mobs away from each other and camp out to clear aggro, then either come right back yourself or have someone in your party pull the closer mob with a cancel magic type spell.  Takes extra time, but splitting mobs with FD sometimes does too.<br>
<br>
Another variation with a CotH mage is to root the mob you want to pull (aggroing everything around it) and KEEP GOING away from the party.  Someone in your party can use a cancel magic spell to pull the rooted one, and then the mage can CotH you which (assuming you're far enough away) will both clear your aggro and bring you back to the fight.<br>
<br>
These tactics don't work on every mob, some you just can't seem to land a root on, but it works a heck of a lot more places than the lull line does. <p><BR>
