</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uskellt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skellt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/02 9:38:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15351.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why did I ever bother spending money on this spell?</span><hr size=1> I don't understand why people expect Pacify to do more than it is supposed to do.  It, just like almost ANY spell, can be resisted.  If resisted it will aggro the mob, just like almost ANY spell.  The benefit of the spell is that if it is NOT resisted, then it does not aggro the mob at all, and lowers that mobs aggro radius for a short time.<br>
<br>
So given that, here is when I use it:  When I am facing a big pull that my party can handle.  This is important:  YOU MUST BE ABLE TO HANDLE THE FULL PULL ALREADY.  Now pull with pacify and sometimes you will get LESS than the full pull and all is great.  If it is resisted, then you get what you expected anyway, and all is good.  If you always use pacify in this specific situation, instead of giving up and using Cancel Magic or Stun or whatever, then you will on average have smaller pulls when breaking.  That is how it works.<br>
<br>
The problem arises when people expect it to work like Harmony, which it doesn't.  Or when they expect it to allow them to break something that their party couldn't handle to begin with.  Then if it gets resisted you are all screwed.  Don't treat it like what its not.<br>
<br>
Now given all that, I personally don't find it very useful.  There's almost always a better way to break.  But I have used it, and I do know when to use it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=15351.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=15351.topic&start=41&stop=43>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=15351.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=15351.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15351.topic&index=20><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=15351.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=15351.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15351.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=15351.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=htt